class WordsRemover(object):
    def __init__(self):
        self.stopwords = set()

    def acquire_stop_words(self, stopwords_file):
        self.stopwords = set([line.strip() for line in
                    open(stopwords_file, 'r', encoding='utf-8').readlines()])

    def remove_stop_words(self, words):
        # remove words in stopwords set
        return [word for word in words if word not in self.stopwords]

import string
import jieba.analyse
from wordcloud import WordCloud, ImageColorGenerator

Month_Trans = {"Jan": "01", "Feb": "02", "Mar": "03", "Apr": "04", "May": "05", "Jun": "06",
               "Jul": "07", "Aug": "08", "Sep": "09", "Oct": "10", "Nov": "11", "Dec": "12"}

def _punctuation() -> Text:
    """

    Returns:
        Punctuation both English and Chinese

    """
    return string.punctuation + '（），。、；‘’【】“”《》：·'


def draw_cloud(text_total: List):
    """Generate word cloud by inputting texts

    Args:
        text_total:
            A list. A list of words.
    Returns:
        A word cloud.

    """
    words_list = [i["text_cut"] for i in text_total]
    
    # join words by " "
    word_blank_split = " ".join(" ".join(word) for word in words_list)

    # set background photo
    mask_img = imageio.imread(background_file)
    image_colors = ImageColorGenerator(mask_img)

    # draw cloud
    cloud = WordCloud(
        max_words=150,
        font_path=font_file,
        background_color='white',
        mask=mask_img
    ).generate(word_blank_split)
    plt.imshow(cloud.recolor(color_func=image_colors))
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.show()

def word_cleaning(text: Text) -> Text:
    """Cleean the word

    Args:
        text:
            A String. The string to be processed.

    Returns:
        A string. With readable Chinese.

    """
    
    # remove content in < > and [ ]
    text = re.sub('<(.*)>', " ", text)
    text = re.sub('\[(.*)\]', " ", text)

    # choose only chinese characters and split the text after join them by " "
    text = ' '.join(re.findall('[\u4e00-\u9fff0-9]+', text))
    
    return text

def word_processing(text: Text, wordsremover: WordsRemover) -> List:
    """PreProcess the word

    Args:
        text:
            A String. The string to be processed.
        wordsremover:
            A words_remover instance. Provide stop words method.
    Returns:
        A list of words processed.

    """
    
    texts = text.split()
    
    words = []
    # cut words by Jieba
    for word in texts:
        words.extend([i for i in jieba.cut(word)])

    # remove stop words
    all_words_stopped = wordsremover.remove_stop_words(words)

    return all_words_stopped

def time_processing(time_raw: Text) -> Text:
    """Acquire text

    Args:
        time_raw:
            A string. Original time.
    Returns:
        A string. Processed time.

    """
    
    return time_raw[-4:] + "-" + Month_Trans[time_raw[4:7]] + "-" + time_raw[8:19]
    
def acquire_text(all_data: List) -> List:
    """Acquire text

    Args:
        all_data:
            A list. The whole json data.
    Returns:
        A list. Text part of data.

    """
    text_total = [{"user_id": i["user"]["id"], "time": i["created_at"], "text": i["text"], "like": i["like_count"]} \
            for i in all_data]
    
    words_remover = WordsRemover()
    words_remover.acquire_stop_words(stopwords_file)

    for text in text_total:
        text["text"] = word_cleaning(text["text"])
        text["text_cut"] = word_processing(text["text"], wordsremover=words_remover)
        text["time"] = time_processing(text["time"])
        text["date"] = text["time"][:10]
    
    return text_total

from mpl_toolkits.basemap import Basemap

cap_pro = pd.read_csv(cap_pro_file, encoding="gb2312", index_col="province")
cap_pro = cap_pro.to_dict()["capital"]

def modify_admin(name: Text) -> Text:
    """Modify the admin name
    
    Args:
        name:
            A string. Original city name.
    Returns:
        A string. New city name.
            
    """
    
    # suffix deleted
    for i in ["自治区","新区", "区","县","自治州","市"]:
        name = name.replace(i,"")
    
    # Administration name changed
    if name == "宣武":
        name = "西城"
    
    if name == "塘沽":
        name = "滨海"
    
    return name
    
def dict_update(name: Text, location_total: Dict) -> Dict:
    """Update the result dictionary
    
    Args:
        name:
            A string. The city name.
        location_total:
            A dictionary. The result dictionary.
            
    Returns:
        A dictionary. The result dictionary.
            
    """
    
    # Province to city
    if name in cap_pro:
        name = modify_admin(cap_pro[name])
    
    if name in location_total:
        location_total[name] = location_total[name] + 1
        
    else:
        # find name without suffix
        if name[:-1] in location_total:
            location_total[name[:-1]] = location_total[name[:-1]] + 1
        else:
            location_total[name] = 1
    
    return location_total

def aggre_location(weibo_id_location: pd.DataFrame) -> Dict:
    """Update the result dictionary
    
    Args:
        weibo_id_location:
            A DataFrame. Input file.
            
    Returns:
        A dictionary. The result dictionary.
            
    """
    
    locations = list(weibo_id_location["location"])

    location_total = {}    

    for location in locations:
        # ignore ""
        if location != "":
            # oversea
            if "海外" in location or "UK" in location or "香港" in location or "澳门" in location or "台湾" in location:
                lot = "境外"
            else:
                # special case of Hainan
                if location == "海南 其他":
                    lot = "海南"
                else:
                    # ignore "未年审"
                    if "未年审" not in location:
                        # company situation
                        if "公司" in location or "社" in location or "工作室" in location or "眼镜店" in location or "照相馆" in location\
                            or "摄影馆" in location or "商行" in location or "官方" in location or "饮品店" in location \
                            or "百货店" in location or "钻石店" in location or "养蜂场" in location:
                            # usually city is in the ()
                            if "(" in location:
                                lot = re.search('\((.*)\)', location).group(1)
                            # or it will be the first two chars
                            else:
                                lot = location[:2]

                            lot = modify_admin(lot)

                        else:
                            loc_spl = location.split()
                            # pro city
                            if len(loc_spl) == 2:
                                lot = loc_spl[1]
                                lot = modify_admin(lot)
                            # city
                            else:
                                lot = loc_spl[0]

            location_total = dict_update(lot, location_total)
    
    return location_total

def draw_center(polygon: List) -> Tuple:
    """Acquire center of a polygon
    
    Args:
        polygon:
            A list. A list of points as a polygon.
            
    Returns:
        A Tuple. The center point.
            
    """

    x = [p[0] for p in polygon]
    y = [p[1] for p in polygon]
    centroid = (sum(x) / len(polygon), sum(y) / len(polygon))
    
    return centroid


def draw_map(location_total: Dict):
    """Draw the map distribution
    
    Args:
        location_total:
            A dictionary. The result ditionary.

    """
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(16,8))
    m = Basemap(
        projection='stere',
        llcrnrlon=79, # left lower point lon
        llcrnrlat=14, # left lower point lat
        urcrnrlon=140,# right upper point lon
        urcrnrlat=52, # right upper point lat
        lon_0=106, # center point lon
        lat_0=34   # center point lat
    )
    
    # country line
    m.drawcountries(linewidth=1, color='#ceceff')
    # background
    m.bluemarble()
    # 1 as the provincial shape
    m.readshapefile(province_shape_file, 'states', drawbounds=True, 
                    linewidth=0.2, color='#ceceff')
    
    # read the lat and lon of each city in China
    lat_lon_df = pd.read_csv(lat_lon_file, encoding='gbk', header=-1)
    lat_lon = {}
    for i, j in lat_lon_df.iterrows():
        lat_lon[j[2]] = {"lat":j[11],"lon":j[10]}
    
    x = []
    y = []
    numbers = []
    error_count = []
    
    # only show the city with more than 100 comments
    location_total_least = {key:value for key,value in location_total.items() if value>100}
    for city, number in location_total_least.items():
        try:
            x.append(lat_lon[city]["lat"])
            y.append(lat_lon[city]["lon"])
            numbers.append(number)
        except KeyError:
            error_count.append((city,number))

    # basemap scatter
    lat = np.array(x)
    lon = np.array(y)
    pop = np.array(numbers,dtype=float)
    size=(pop/np.max(pop))*1100
    x,y = m(lon,lat)
    m.scatter(x,y,s=size, color="#D7DBDD", alpha=0.6)
    plt.title('Weibo Commenter Distribution')
    plt.show()

from snownlp import SnowNLP

def word_sentiment(text_total: List) -> List:
    """Calculate sentiment value of each text row

    Args:
        text_total:
            A list. The whole json data.
    Returns:
        A list. Text part of data with sentimetn value.

    """
    
    for texts in text_total:
        texts["sentiment"] = np.mean([SnowNLP(text).sentiments for text in texts["text"].split()])
    
    return text_total

import matplotlib.dates as mdates
from collections import Counter
lower = -600
upper = -300

def wavg(df: pd.DataFrame, value_column: Text, weight_column:Text) -> SupportsFloat:
    """Define a weighted average rule.

    Args:
        df:
            A dataframe.
        value_column:
            A string. The column with value to average.
        weight_column:
            A string. The column with weights.

    Returns:
        A float. The weighted average result.

    """
    
    values = df[value_column]
    weights = df[weight_column]
    try:
        return (values * weights).sum() / weights.sum()
    except ZeroDivisionError:
        return values.mean()

# Not in use now
def stringsum(df: pd.DataFrame, str_column: Text) -> Text:
    """Define a string sum function.

    Args:
        df:
            A dataframe.
        str_column:
            A string. The column with strings to sum.

    Returns:
        A string. The result of sum string.

    """
    
    strings = df[str_column].tolist()
    
    combine_string = []
    for string in strings:
        try:
            combine_string.append(string.replace(" ","。"))
        except:
            pass
        
    return "。".join(combine_string)

def listextend(df: pd.DataFrame, list_column: Text) -> Text:
    """Define a string sum function.

    Args:
        df:
            A dataframe.
        list_column:
            A string. The column with list to extend.

    Returns:
        A text. The result of extending list.

    """

    lists = df[list_column].tolist()
    
    combine_list = []
    for lst in lists:
        lst = lst.replace("[", "").replace("]","").replace("'","").split(", ")
        if "" in lst:
            lst.remove("")

        combine_list.extend(lst)

    try:
        # find the most frequency word in special day as the main topic
        return " ".join([i[0] for i in Counter(combine_list).most_common(3)])
    except IndexError:
        return "None"

def sentiment_draw(sentiment_total: pd.DataFrame):
    """Draw sentiment plot by showing the main topic in the special positive or negative day.

    Args:
        df:
            A dataframe. Columns, i.e. user_id, date, text, text_cut, sentiment, like.
    """
    
    # group date by weighted sentiment value
    sentiment_dates = sentiment_total.groupby("date").apply(wavg, "sentiment", "like")[lower:upper].to_frame()
    sentiment_dates.columns = ["sentiment"]
    sentiment_dates.index = pd.to_datetime(sentiment_dates.index)

    # group date and find topic that day
    sentiment_text = sentiment_total.groupby("date").apply(listextend, "text_cut")[lower:upper]
    sentiment_text.index = pd.to_datetime(sentiment_text.index)

    ax = sentiment_dates.plot(title = "Weibo Sentiment Tendency")
    ax.set_ylabel("Sentiment Value")
    ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(plt.FixedFormatter(sentiment_dates.index.strftime('%m/%d/%Y')))
    
    # show thee topic
    texts = []
    for number, items in list(sentiment_dates["sentiment"].items()):
        if abs(items-0.5) > 0.20:
            texts.append(ax.text(number, items, sentiment_text[number], fontproperties=ChineseFont, fontsize=20))
    
    # good function to make text not covering each other
    adjust_text(texts)
